10/12/2002
MADRID, Spain -- Prime Minister José María Aznar expressed his support for Cyprus' bid to enter the EU, after meeting Monday (9 December) with Greek Prime Minister Costas Simitis.
Aznar added that efforts to solve the Cyprus issue should continue even after the EU summit later this week in Copenhagen.
For his part, Simitis said that Turkey had to make some compromises on the issue in order to achieve progress.
Greece assumes the EU's rotating presidency on 1 January.
(Athens News Agency, Macedonian Press Agency - 09/12/02)
